## Project Structure (generated by `odin new` + manual setup)

**Base structure after `odin new`:**
```
<project-name>/
  src/
    app/
      app.component.ts       ← Main component
      app.component.html     ← Main template
      app.component.css      ← Main styles
      app.module.ts          ← Root module
    assets/
    environments/
  angular.json
  package.json
  tsconfig.json
  odin.json                  ← Odin/M3 proxy configuration
```

**Recommended structure after manual setup (create these folders):**
```
<project-name>/
  src/
    app/
      app.component.ts
      app.component.html
      app.component.css
      app.module.ts
      services/              ← CREATE THIS: M3 API services
        data.service.ts      ← Example: main data service
        item.service.ts      ← Example: item-specific service
      models/                ← CREATE THIS: TypeScript interfaces
      types/                 ← CREATE THIS: Type definitions
        item.interface.ts    ← Example: IItem interface
      components/            ← CREATE THIS: Reusable components (if needed)
    assets/
    environments/
```

**For larger projects, follow the feature-based structure from `Projects Examples/`:**
```
src/app/
  core/
    services/       ← Global services
    models/         ← Shared models
    types/          ← Global types
  features/
    <feature-name>/
      components/   ← Feature components
      services/     ← Feature-specific services
      types/        ← Feature types
  shared/
    components/     ← Shared UI components
```

